City Power says technicians are working on fixing the failure after implementing a load rotation yesterday to ease the heavy electricity. JOHANNESBURG - City Power says electricity will be restored this morning north eastern parts of Johannesburg following a transformation failure at the Sebenza Substation. It's understood the technical fault happened on Wednesday resulting in the total loss of generation at Kelvin Power Station. City Power says technicians are working on fixing the failure after implementing a load rotation yesterday to ease the heavy electricity. Spokesperson Sandiso Simelane said, “The load rotation continues as we anticipate full restoration.”